And I posted this earlier, just a random “just got new hair pic” and a few comments really got to me so I just deleted it. Usually I’m not bothered.  But a few, “why is your face fuller now?” And I was pissed!  First off, who says that?!! Second off, when people look back at older videos or pics of mine…I was 95 lbs, in an unhealthy relationship, had no self esteem, and was used to being put down. 
Well guess what, years have past…I’m not 95 lbs anymore and I’m in a healthy relationship where I’m happy and happy with myself as I am. 
People on social media need to realize words can be more then words sometimes.  You don’t know the person who’s picture you’re commenting on.  You don’t know what that person has been through, or is going through.  Maybe someone super skinny is not healthy, is depressed, is struggling internally…but all you see is she’s skinny. 
Wake up and realize no one on social media needs to be critiqued by anyone else.  We are all just living our life how WE want to.  Worry about your face, worry about how you want to do your hair, worry about YOU….and stop judging others or even caring about things that don’t effect you. 
We need to be better.  We need to be kinder to others.  We have a young generation growing up looking at social media…don’t show them bullying or disrespect.  This is exactly why I don’t let my kids on social media…why expose them at a vulnerable age to unnecessary comments they don’t need. 
It’s 2023…let’s all grow up and spread positivity ✌️

What is Glycation and How to Reverse it 💯…

Glycation is a naturally occurring chemical reaction that causes sugar molecules such as glucose to bind to proteins and lipids throughout the body including the skin. The result is the formation of advanced glycation end products, or AGE’s.  When this occurs, the proteins and lipids involved in the glycation process become damaged and therefore unable to perform their normal functions properly. 
When these sugar molecules bind to the collagen and elastin proteins in the skin, they breakdown the healthy collagen and elastin which in turn weakens the skin healthy support and structure.  This leads to premature aging and wrinkles, and crepey skin, and lose of elasticity. 
A number of factors cause glycation in the skin. Diets high in sugar, stress, oxidative stress, uv exposure, air pollution, and poor lifestyle habits. 

Reverse and slow glycation by using targeted skincare made specifically to reduce glycation effects.  The listed in this post are amazing! (Skinceuticals AGE eye complex is my go to for the eye area!). You also need to use your antioxidants and retinoids daily as well as a good skin barrier repair product. 

Also reduce your sugar intake, use your spf daily and take supplements that reduce oxidative stress in the body. 

Pair a healthy lifestyle with proper skincare and supplements and you can combat and reverse the effects of glycation!
